%section#whatson
  .row
    .small-12.columns.text-center
      %h2.longborder What&rsquo;s on?
        
      :markdown
        The festival launches on **Friday** at the Lesbian and Gay Foundation, with the **[inaugural Allan Horsfall lecture](/blog/2014/11/13/allan-horsfall-lecture.html)**, sponsored by the Campagin for Homosexual Equality. **Saturday** at **Central Library** goes _Under The Rainbow_, with an exploration of LGBT identity and personal stories from the 18th century to today. **Sunday** at **People's History Musuem** explores lesbian activists, LGBT rights in the workplace, and explores Britain's colonial legacy in exporting homophobic laws.

        **[_A Very Victorian Scandal_](#theatre)**, our innovative, immersive theatre performance based on an 1880 police raid on a fancy dress ball, runs throughout the weekend. There are **family-friendly** events for children and young adults on the Saturday and Sunday. The 2nd **&ldquo;What is and how to do LGBT history&rdquo;** conference runs in parallel at the **Lesbian and Gay Foundation**.

        Finally, there are **films** throughout the week in Manchester's **Gay Village**, and various suprises in the week leading up to the festival. Stay tuned, and be sure to follow our [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/lgbthistoryfestival?fref=ts) and [Twitter](https://twitter.com/lgbthistoryfest), or join our [e-mail list](http://crm.lgbthistoryfestival.org/civicrm/mailing/subscribe) for up-to-the minute news! Keep scrolling to find out more, or go to the [schedule page](/schedule.html) to find out full details.
